name: A perfluorocarbon-cured elastomer (PCE) produced by terpolymerizing tetrafluoroethylene
perfluoro(2,5-dimethyl-3,6-dioxanone vinyl ether)
and perfluoro (6,6-dihydro-6-iodo-3-oxa-1-hexene)

FoodContactSubstance: A perfluorocarbon-cured elastomer (PCE) produced by terpolymerizing tetrafluoroethylene (CAS Reg. No. 116-14-3), perfluoro(2,5-dimethyl-3,6-dioxanone vinyl ether) (CAS Reg. No. 2599-84-0) and perfluoro (6,6-dihydro-6-iodo-3-oxa-1-hexene) (CAS Reg. No. 106108-22-9) and subsequent curing of the terpolymer (CAS Reg. No. 106108-23-0) by crosslinking with triallylcyanurate (CAS Reg. No. 101-37-1) and vulcanizing with 2,5-dimethyl-2,5-di(t-butylperoxy) hexane (CAS Reg. No. 78-63-7), as a 68% dispersion on finely divided silica
